# Bondi – Terms of Use & Privacy Policy  
**Updated:** 01 October 2025

Welcome to Bondi. By creating an account or using our services, you agree to the following Terms of Use and Privacy Policy. Please read carefully before registering.

---

## 1. Eligibility
- You must be at least 18 years old to use Bondi.  
- You must provide accurate information, including your date of birth, gender, and height.  
- Accounts with false or misleading information may be suspended or removed.  
- We do not knowingly allow use of Bondi by minors under 18. If discovered, such accounts will be deleted immediately.  

---

## 2. Registration & Verification
- To access browsing and matching features, you must complete Bondi’s selfie verification process.  
- The verification selfie is processed locally on your device and is **not stored** on Bondi’s servers.  
- If you reinstall Bondi or switch devices, you must retake the selfie to regain verified status.  

---

## 3. Data We Collect
- **Account Data:** email address, password, phone number, date of birth, gender.  
- **Profile Data:** name, bio, height, photos, selected interests, and preferences.  
- **Location Data:** approximate city-level location (based on your provided settings).  
- **Interactions:** likes, dislikes, favorites, matches, messages, blocks, reports.  
- **Technical Data:** only a timestamp of your last activity and a Firebase Cloud Messaging token for notifications.  
- **Verification Data:** your selfie is processed only locally for verification.  

---

## 4. How We Use Your Data
- Provide browsing, matching, and messaging services.  
- Enable filters (age, height, distance).  
- Maintain safety, including blocking, reporting, and moderation.  
- Improve the app experience through user feedback.  

**Legal bases under GDPR:**  
- Contractual necessity (to provide our services).  
- Legitimate interest (safety, fraud prevention, moderation).  
- Consent (optional features such as photo uploads and interests).  

---

## 5. Data Storage & Sharing
- We do **not sell** your data.  
- Limited data (e.g., FCM tokens) is shared with Google Firebase for notifications.  
- Profile and interaction data are stored securely on Google Firestore and MongoDB Atlas.  
- Public profile photos are hosted by Imgur and may be accessible via public URLs.  
- Depending on your location, we may use EU or US servers for better performance.  
- Moderation reports may be reviewed by trusted third-party services for safety.  
- Data transfers outside the EU/EEA (e.g., to the US) use legal safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs).  

---

## 6. Safety, Conduct & Content
- Be respectful, honest, and lawful when using Bondi.  
- Do not harass, abuse, impersonate, or exploit other users.  
- Do not post illegal, harmful, hateful, or explicit content.  
- Only upload appropriate photos.  
- You can block or report users who behave inappropriately.  
- Do not click external links shared by users.  
- Bondi reserves the right to suspend or remove accounts that violate these terms.  

---

## 7. Your Rights (GDPR / EEA Users)
If you are located in the EU/EEA, you have the right to:
- Access your stored personal data.  
- Request deletion of your account and associated data.  
- Correct or update inaccurate information.  
- Export your data (data portability).  
- Withdraw consent, where applicable.  
- Block or report other users safely within the app.  

Requests can be made via in-app support or by email at **bondi.dating@gmail.com**.

---

## 8. Data Retention & Account Deletion
- All user data is deleted when an account is deleted.  
- We do not retain data beyond this point, except as required for legal obligations (e.g., fraud or abuse reports).  
- Inactive accounts may be paused after 30 days and permanently deleted after 6 months.  

---

## 9. Subscriptions & Payments
- Some features are premium and require payment via Google Play.  
- Subscriptions renew automatically unless cancelled.  
- Refunds follow Google Play’s refund policy.  

---

## 10. Liability & Disclaimers
- Bondi is provided “as is” without warranties of any kind.  
- We are not responsible for the behavior of other users, nor for offline meetings or relationships formed.  
- Users are solely responsible for the content they share.  

---

## 11. Governing Law & Disputes
- These Terms are governed by the laws of the European Union and Estonia.  
- Disputes are handled by Estonian courts, unless EU law requires otherwise.  

---

## 12. Changes to Terms
- We may update these Terms and Privacy Policy.  
- Significant changes will be communicated in-app.  
- Continued use of Bondi means you accept the revised terms.  

---

If you do not agree to these Terms, please do not create an account.  
For any questions, contact: **bondi.dating@gmail.com**
